Fix Bookings dialog white-screen, remove leaked Google credentials, harden post-merge

User report: clicking the new "Bookings" button on a project showed a
white screen with the page auto-refreshing.

Bookings dialog (client/src/components/Projects/ProjectDetail.jsx):
- Hardened loadBookingRows so an unexpected/partial response from
  /api/projects/:id/booking/rows can no longer crash the dialog. The
  payload is now normalised: rows are coerced to plain objects with
  string-only cell values (objects/arrays JSON-stringified), counts are
  coerced to finite numbers, and tabName/sheetUrl/returned defaulted.
  Any error from the call is logged to the console and surfaced in the
  dialog rather than bubbling up.
- Tightened the per-project "Custom rules & instructions for the AI"
  textarea label, placeholder examples, and helper copy.

Security (critical, user must rotate):
- Discovered a Google service-account private key (private_key_id
  9a806c3a01...) committed in two places:
    1. .replit -> [userenv.shared] GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON (full JSON)
    2. attached_assets/gen-lang-client-0941709967-9a806c3a0122_*.json
- Removed the env var via deleteEnvVars (the value also exists as a
  proper Replit Secret, so backend keeps working).
- Deleted the JSON file from attached_assets/.
- Added .gitignore patterns for service-account JSON files
  (gen-lang-client-*.json, *service-account*.json, *-credentials*.json)
  to prevent recurrence.
- Told the user (in chat) to revoke that key in Google Cloud Console
  and upload a fresh JSON into the GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON secret.

Post-merge setup:
- Added scripts/post-merge.sh (installs server + client deps, set -e,
  non-interactive) and registered it via setPostMergeConfig so the
  HOOK_NOT_FOUND error after task merges no longer fires.

Backend restarted cleanly after env var removal; client builds clean.
